**Version Used**: Visual Studio 15.7.6

**Steps to Reproduce**:

```C#
using System.Collections.Generic;
using Windows.UI.Xaml.Controls;

static class Example
{
    public static readonly Dictionary<int, string> Icons = new Dictionary<int, string>
    {
        [(int)Symbol.Accept] = "accept.png",
    };
}
```

**Expected Behavior**: Don't suggest removing the cast to int

**Actual Behavior**: Visual Studio suggests removing the cast to int, which results in a compile error.

Resolved the problem with reversing of generated unwind info in the object file. See the latest comment in https://github.com/dotnet/corert/issues/5874

